<ul>
  <li><a href="http://postdoc.jhu.edu">JHU Homewood Office of Postdoctoral Affairs</a> - info on orientation, services/benefits (healthcare, dental, life insurance, etc), the postdoc association, and more</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="for-phd-students">For PhD Students</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.bme.jhu.edu/graduate/phd/resources/">JHU BME PhD student resources</a> - info on PhD requirements and more</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="for-international-students">For International Students</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://ois.jhu.edu/">JHU Office of International Services</a> - info on immigration/Visas, legal assistance, and more</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="other">Other</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://studentaffairs.jhu.edu/student-life/diversity-inclusion/">JHU Offices for Diversity and Inclusion</a> - includes links and info on The Office of Multicultural Affairs, Religious and Spiritual Life, Womand and Gender Resources, LGBTQ Life, Center for Disability Services, and more</li>
  <li><a href="https://studentaffairs.jhu.edu/student-health/">JHU Student Health and Wellness Center</a> - all our full-time, part-time and visiting undergraduate and graduate students as well as post-docatoral fellows are eligible to receive high quality, confidential health care through the Student Health and Wellness Center</li>
  <li><a href="https://hr.jhu.edu/benefits-worklife/">JHU Benefits and Worklife</a> - resources for family-focused programs, wellness courses, community engagement, and more</li>
</ul>

